  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your comments and I would like to extend our sincere apologises that you and the person you accompanied had such a long wait to be seen. All patients who attend the ED  via ambulance or walk ins  are triaged using the Manchester triage tool this is a national framework to categorise patients according to medical need. The nurse will ask a series of questions and conduct a short physical examination the nurse will then afford the patients a category, these are;

• P1 – TO BE SEEN IMMEDIATELY
• P2 – TO BE SEEN WITHIN 20 MINS
• P3 TO BE SEEN WITHIN 1 HR
• P4- TO BE SEEN WITHIN 2HRS

We apologise that due to a number of doctor shortages patients have been waiting longer to be seen.

There is  a plan for the ED to be renovated and this work will start over the next 2-3 years, until then we continue to make changes to ensure that patients have a compassionate journey through the department. Your comments around signage have been forwarded to the Director of Estates and facilities

Kind Regards

Head of Nursing
Emergency Department QEH

